Lavrentev, –≤—ã—à–ª–∞ —Å—Ç–∞—Ç—å—è "Electrochemical platform for detecting Escherichia coli bacteria using machine learning methods" –≤ –∂—É—Ä–Ω–∞–ª–µ "Biosensors and Bioelectronics" —Å impact factor 12, —É—á–∞—Å—Ç–≤–æ–≤–∞–ª –≤ —Å–º–µ–Ω–µ –ó–µ—Ä–∫–∞–ª—å–Ω–æ–≥–æ, –∫–æ–Ω–∫—É—Ä—Å–∞—Ö "–°–∏—Ä–∏—É—Å.–õ–µ—Ç–æ", "–±–æ–ª—å—à–∏–µ –≤—ã–∑–æ–≤—ã". –î–ª—è —Å—Ç–∞—Ç—å–∏ —è –ø—Ä–æ–≤–µ–ª –º–Ω–æ–≥–æ –∏—Å—Å–ª–µ–¥–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–π, –Ω–∞–ø–∏—Å–∞–ª –ø–µ—Ä–≤—ã–µ —á–µ—Ä–Ω–æ–≤–∏–∫–∏ —Å—Ç–∞—Ç—å–∏ –∏ –≤ –∫–æ–Ω—Ü–µ –Ω–∞–ø–∏—à–∏, —á—Ç–æ —è —Å—á–∏—Ç–∞—é —Å–µ–±—è –¥–æ—Å—Ç–æ–π–Ω—ã–º –ø–æ–ª—É—á–∏—Ç—å infochemistry scholarship. 

–í–æ—Ç –ø—Ä–∏–º–µ—Ä motivation letter –º–æ–µ–≥–æ –Ω–∞—É—á–Ω–æ–≥–æ —Ä—É–∫–æ–≤–æ–¥–∏—Ç–µ–ª—è:
I am a 2nd-year master's student in the Infochemistry Scientific Center at the ITMO
University.
Scientific work is a complex and laborious process for which the appearance of fresh ideas
and the will to implement them is very important. ISC scholarship is a powerful material and
motivational support for students engaged in such work. I always see that it allows you to throw
all your strength into getting good results, as well as devote as much time to scientific projects as
possible.
I started working on my scientific project back in November last year, while simultaneously
combining it with another. My project was related to the development of an electrochemical sensor
system for the detection of lactic acid bacteria using machine learning algorithms. This flexible
sensor electronics project is interesting, and the results are promising. In the process of working
on the project, I and Igor Rumyantsev collected a lot of data on the current-voltage characteristics
of the bacteria Streptococcus thermophilus and Bacillus coagulans at various concentrations. I,
Artemii Ivanov, and Vladimir Shilovskikh have studied various chemical processes at the
hydrogel/electrode interface and calculated various thermodynamic values. And I also chose the
most effective machine learning algorithm and algorithm parameters for predicting the bacterial
composition of analytes.
In the course of my work, I got acquainted with the work on a scanning electron microscope
with energy-dispersive X-ray spectroscopy and learned how to calculate Density Functional
Theory. The results of the study were submitted to several journals (ACS Analytical Chemistry ‚Äì
IF 6.98, Advanced Functional Materials ‚Äì IF 18.8, Nature Methods ‚Äì IF 28.4) but subsequently
published in ACS Applied Materials & Interfaces (IF ‚Äì 9.2).
Although this project can be considered complete, I still continue to work in the field of
self-growing and self-organizing electronics. All of my work steps require focus, interest, and
strong analytical skills from me. But of course, I, like any other student, have small extraneous
questions that distract me from research and such funding will help me solve them. It will be a
great help for me in my work and study. If I become a winner, I will get the opportunity to more
freely dispose of my resources and allow me to complete the experiments and write articles double-
quick.

–í–æ—Ç –ø—Ä–∏–º–µ—Ä motivation letter –º–æ–µ–≥–æ –Ω–∞—É—á–Ω–æ–≥–æ —Ä—É–∫–æ–≤–æ–¥–∏—Ç–µ–ª—è:
I am a 2nd-year master's student in the Infochemistry Scientific Center at the ITMO
University.
Scientific work is a complex and laborious process for which the appearance of fresh ideas
and the will to implement them is very important. ISC scholarship is a powerful material and
motivational support for students engaged in such work. I always see that it allows you to throw
all your strength into getting good results, as well as devote as much time to scientific projects as
possible.
I started working on my scientific project back in November last year, while simultaneously
combining it with another. My project was related to the development of an electrochemical sensor
system for the detection of lactic acid bacteria using machine learning algorithms. This flexible
sensor electronics project is interesting, and the results are promising. In the process of working
on the project, I and Igor Rumyantsev collected a lot of data on the current-voltage characteristics
of the bacteria Streptococcus thermophilus and Bacillus coagulans at various concentrations. I,
Artemii Ivanov, and Vladimir Shilovskikh have studied various chemical processes at the
hydrogel/electrode interface and calculated various thermodynamic values. And I also chose the
most effective machine learning algorithm and algorithm parameters for predicting the bacterial
composition of analytes.
In the course of my work, I got acquainted with the work on a scanning electron microscope
with energy-dispersive X-ray spectroscopy and learned how to calculate Density Functional
Theory. The results of the study were submitted to several journals (ACS Analytical Chemistry ‚Äì
IF 6.98, Advanced Functional Materials ‚Äì IF 18.8, Nature Methods ‚Äì IF 28.4) but subsequently
published in ACS Applied Materials & Interfaces (IF ‚Äì 9.2).
Although this project can be considered complete, I still continue to work in the field of
self-growing and self-organizing electronics. All of my work steps require focus, interest, and
strong analytical skills from me. But of course, I, like any other student, have small extraneous
questions that distract me from research and such funding will help me solve them. It will be a
great help for me in my work and study. If I become a winner, I will get the opportunity to more
freely dispose of my resources and allow me to complete the experiments and write articles double-
quick.

Dear Members of the Scholarship Committee,

My name is Alexandr Vladimirovich Dyakonov, and I am currently a second-year bachelor's student at the Infochemistry Scientific Center at ITMO University. I am writing to express my strong interest in the Infochemistry Scholarship, which I believe will significantly support my ongoing scientific endeavors and future aspirations.

Scientific research is a challenging and intricate process that requires a continuous influx of innovative ideas and a steadfast commitment to realizing them. The Infochemistry Scholarship stands as a crucial source of both financial and motivational support for students engaged in rigorous scientific work. It offers the invaluable opportunity to devote undivided attention to research projects, enabling the achievement of outstanding results.

My journey in scientific research began in the 11th grade under the guidance of my esteemed supervisor, Filipp V. Lavrentev. For the past three years, I have dedicated myself to a project focused on the development of an electrochemical platform for detecting Escherichia coli bacteria using machine learning methods. This work culminated in the publication of a research paper titled "Electrochemical platform for detecting Escherichia coli bacteria using machine learning methods" in the prestigious journal "Biosensors and Bioelectronics," which boasts an impact factor of 12.

Throughout the duration of this project, I have immersed myself in extensive research, including conducting numerous experiments, analyzing data, and drafting the initial manuscripts for the paper. This project not only honed my technical skills but also deepened my understanding of the interdisciplinary nature of infochemistry, blending principles of chemistry, biology, and artificial intelligence.

In addition to my primary research, I have actively participated in various scientific programs and competitions, such as the Zerkalniy shift, "Sirius.Summer," and "Big Challenges." These experiences have broadened my perspective and fostered a collaborative spirit, reinforcing my dedication to advancing scientific knowledge.

I firmly believe that I am a deserving candidate for the Infochemistry Scholarship. This scholarship will allow me to focus entirely on my research, alleviating financial constraints and enabling me to explore new dimensions in the field of infochemistry. It will also empower me to contribute more effectively to the scientific community by accelerating the completion of experiments and the publication of additional research articles.

Thank you for considering my application. I am confident that with your support, I will be able to make significant contributions to the field of infochemistry and continue on the path of scientific discovery.

Sincerely,

Alexandr Vladimirovich Dyakonov
Bachelor's Student, Infochemistry Scientific Center
ITMO University
